
--------------------------------------------------
ConnectX-6Dx CC  Simulation - ccsim
--------------------------------------------------

Ccsim simulator enables Congestion Control algorithm development.
The simulator is built using OMNET++.
It contains the following ingredients:
		omnetpp.ini - configuration file of the simulation parameters that can be
			          modified by the user. (Network parameters, Traffic patterns, 
                                  Algorithms parameters)
		ccsim_release - executables of the simulation in 
			                                                release and debug mode.

--------------
Installation
--------------

To install the simulator type "source NVIDIACCSimSetup" in the top folder of the
simulation (NVIDIACCsim-<release date>)

----------------------------
Common commands
----------------------------

Run the simulation from sim directory 

run command: 
	../bin/ccsim_release omnetpp.ini -c <Config> -r <Run number>
	
	Config is one of the configurations that appear in omnetpp.ini file.
	To see all the configurations type:
			../bin/ccsim_release omnetpp.ini -a
	
	Run number - determines the number of Hosts and QPs in the system.
	To see detailed list of all the runs of a configuration type:  
		../bin/ccsim_release omnetpp.ini -x <Config> -g
		
		
Example of running RL in simultaneous many to one traffic pattern with two hosts and 
one QP per host:
	../bin/ccsim_release omnetpp.ini -c RL_Simult_ManyToOne -r 0
	